==English==
===Adjective===
{{wikipediaAlt|Caucasian race}}
[[Category:English adjectives]]
'''Caucasian'''

Caucasian , ( also called white) refers to people who originally came from The Caucus area in Eastern Europe( Armenia ) and then they spread to other lands such as Europe , Russia , America , etc.. Hence Armenians are known and have been known world over as "The Original White People " .

#(''anthropology'') of a [[human]] [[racial]] [[classification]]; including [[people]]s of [[Europe]], [[Northern]] [[Africa]], [[Western]] [[Asia]], [[Southern Asia]] and parts of [[Central Asia]] having very light to brown pigmented skin.
#of, or relating to the [[Caucasus]] [[region]] or its [[people]], [[language]]s and [[culture]].

People of Armenia and of Armenian decent . ( First occupants of Caucus , where the term Caucasian comes from where and still are the Armenians .)

